By Patrick Ochoga, Benin City The Chairman and the Chief Executive Officer, Ocean Marine Solutions, OMSL, Capt Idahosa Wells Okunbo, has expressed his satisfaction so far with the conduct the Edo gubernatorial Election and calls for calmness as the process continues in order to be able to elect a governor that will bring about a better Edo State. Captian Hosa who spoke to newsmen shortly after casting his vote at George Idah primary School, Ihama, G.R.A Benin City at about 11.58am, said he is satisfied with the peace nation so far. In his words, ”I am very happy because everywhere is calm, everywhere is peaceful and this is what we have been praying for, no antagonisms, no oppression as far as I can see around here, I thank God for today, it’s a day we have all waited for. “I pray that God will do his own, that’s what I am praying for, a better Edo State, Edo State that is devoid of oppression, Edo State that our children can be once more employed in the real way, positively and a Positive change for our children.” It will be recalled that the Business Mogul recently address some Senior Media Editors where he openly throws his weight behind the Candidate of the All Progressive Congress Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu. 